Exploration/exploitation tradeoff

Notion of improvement

Def: the improvement for a design \(\mathbf{x}\) is given by the function \(I: \mathbf{x} \in D \mapsto \max( \min_{1 \leq i \leq n} f(\mathbf{x_i})) - Y(\mathbf{x}), 0)\).

In case of a GP, the improvement at \(x\) is a random variable.

Probability of Improvement: \[PI(x) = \mathbb{P}[Y(x) \leq t_n| \mathbf{X}_n, \mathbf{Y}_n] = \Phi \left( \frac{t_n - m_n(x)}{s_n(x)} \right)\] with \(t_n = \min \limits_{1 \leq i \leq n} y_i\).

Expected Improvement: \[E[I(\textbf{x})|\mathbf{X}_n, \mathbf{Y}_n ] = \left(t_n - m_n(\textbf{x})\right)\Phi\left(\frac{t_n - m_n(\textbf{x})}{s_n(\textbf{x})} \right)+s_n(\textbf{x})\phi\left(\frac{t_n - m_n(\textbf{x})}{s_n(\textbf{x})} \right)\] where \(\phi\) and \(\Phi\) are the pdf and cdf of the standard Gaussian law.
